{
  "texts": [
    "This involves questions about shifting liability from users to producers despite producers' limited control over AI systems 5 While EU product liability is generally thought of as strict liability, the limitation of liability to defective products has aspects of a negligence test.",
    "Defectiveness is a negligence element in the sense that the producer is not liable for any harm caused by their products like an insurer would (Wendel, 2019, 391), but only for harm caused by defective products.",
    "This criterion, however, differs from a typical negligence rule because the manufacturer is liable regardless of whether the manufacturer is to blame for the defect (Li & Visscher, 2020, 7).",
    "See further Sect. 3.1.",
    "6 Or even a no-liability rule, if in practice harmed parties are often unable to prove the defect."
  ]
}